{"filename":"getting-started.md","title":"Getting started","headings":[{"level":2,"text":"What is a build process?","id":"what-is-a-build-process"},{"level":2,"text":"Installing Node.js & npm","id":"installing-nodejs--npm"},{"level":2,"text":"Using PostCSS CLI","id":"using-postcss-cli"},{"level":2,"text":"Alternatives to using the CLI","id":"alternatives-to-using-the-cli"},{"level":3,"text":"Grunt","id":"grunt"},{"level":3,"text":"Gulp","id":"gulp"},{"level":3,"text":"Webpack","id":"webpack"},{"level":3,"text":"Others","id":"others"}],"layout":"Guide","order":2,"body":{"t":"div","c":[{"t":"h2","p":{"id":"what-is-a-build-process"},"c":[{"t":"a","p":{"aria-hidden":"true","href":"#what-is-a-build-process"},"c":[{"t":"span","p":{"class":"icon icon-link"}}]},"What is a build process?"]},"\n",{"t":"p","c":["A build process is a sequence of tasks, usually automated, that you run each\ntime that you want to deploy a new release of your application. cssnano fits\ninto this build process as a tool that should be run on your development CSS,\nand in turn will create compressed production assets. These are then uploaded\nto your production server or CDN."]},"\n",{"t":"p","c":["There are a number of different ways that you can compose a build process; we\nrecommend using the command line, but you might also want to consider an\nabstraction such as ",{"t":"a","p":{"href":"http://gulpjs.com/"},"c":["gulp"]},", especially for more complex\nsystems."]},"\n",{"t":"h2","p":{"id":"installing-nodejs--npm"},"c":[{"t":"a","p":{"aria-hidden":"true","href":"#installing-nodejs--npm"},"c":[{"t":"span","p":{"class":"icon icon-link"}}]},"Installing Node.js & npm"]},"\n",{"t":"p","c":["cssnano is installed using the command line, using ",{"t":"a","p":{"href":"https://npmjs.com"},"c":["npm"]},"; so\nyou will need to use an application such as Terminal or the Windows Command\nPrompt. If you don't already have Node.js installed, then you'll need to\nfollow these instructions:"]},"\n",{"t":"p","c":["We require a minimum of Node.js version 6.9.0 & npm 3.10.8 to run, and we\nrecommend that you install ",{"t":"a","p":{"href":"https://github.com/creationix/nvm"},"c":["nvm"]}," to manage\nyour Node.js versions."]},"\n",{"t":"p","c":["Alternately, you can ",{"t":"a","p":{"href":"https://nodejs.org/en/"},"c":["visit the Node.js website"]}," and\nfollow the instructions there to install it for your machine."]},"\n",{"t":"p","c":["Once you have installed Node.js & npm, you can run this command to install\ncssnano into your project:"]},"\n",{"t":"pre","p":{"class":"editor editor-colors"},"c":[{"t":"div","p":{"class":"line"},"c":[{"t":"span","p":{"class":"syntax--text syntax--plain syntax--null-grammar"},"c":[{"t":"span","c":["npm install cssnano --save-dev"]}]}]}]},"\n",{"t":"p","c":["Note that for most typical setups, we recommend that you compress your CSS\nduring your deployment step, so that when it is uploaded to your server/CDN\nit is already optimized. In most cases, you should not need to install cssnano\non your web server."]},"\n",{"t":"h2","p":{"id":"using-postcss-cli"},"c":[{"t":"a","p":{"aria-hidden":"true","href":"#using-postcss-cli"},"c":[{"t":"span","p":{"class":"icon icon-link"}}]},"Using PostCSS CLI"]},"\n",{"t":"p","c":["Once you have cssnano installed, you will need a PostCSS runner in order to\nuse it to compress your CSS files. We recommend the PostCSS command line module,\nbut you can use any of the alternatives listed in the next section."]},"\n",{"t":"p","c":["You can install ",{"t":"a","p":{"href":"https://github.com/postcss/postcss-cli"},"c":["PostCSS CLI"]},"\nwith this command:"]},"\n",{"t":"pre","p":{"class":"editor editor-colors"},"c":[{"t":"div","p":{"class":"line"},"c":[{"t":"span","p":{"class":"syntax--text syntax--plain syntax--null-grammar"},"c":[{"t":"span","c":["npm install postcss-cli --global"]}]}]}]},"\n",{"t":"p","c":["Once you have done this, you will need to configure cssnano by creating a\n",{"t":"code","c":["postcss.config.js"]}," file in the root of your project. This should contain\ncssnano as well as any other ",{"t":"a","p":{"href":"https://github.com/postcss/postcss/blob/master/site/plugins.md"},"c":["plugins"]}," that you might want for your project;\nas an example:"]},"\n",{"t":"pre","p":{"class":"editor editor-colors"},"c":[{"t":"div","p":{"class":"line"},"c":[{"t":"span","p":{"class":"syntax--source syntax--js"},"c":[{"t":"span","p":{"class":"syntax--support syntax--variable syntax--js"},"c":[{"t":"span","c":["module"]}]},{"t":"span","p":{"class":"syntax--meta syntax--delimiter syntax--property syntax--period syntax--js"},"c":[{"t":"span","c":["."]}]},{"t":"span","p":{"class":"syntax--variable syntax--other syntax--property syntax--js"},"c":[{"t":"span","c":["exports"]}]},{"t":"span","c":[" "]},{"t":"span","p":{"class":"syntax--keyword syntax--operator syntax--assignment syntax--js"},"c":[{"t":"span","c":["="]}]},{"t":"span","c":[" "]},{"t":"span","p":{"class":"syntax--meta syntax--brace syntax--curly syntax--js"},"c":[{"t":"span","c":["{"]}]}]}]},{"t":"div","p":{"class":"line"},"c":[{"t":"span","p":{"class":"syntax--source syntax--js"},"c":[{"t":"span","c":["    plugins"]},{"t":"span","p":{"class":"syntax--keyword syntax--operator syntax--assignment syntax--js"},"c":[{"t":"span","c":[":"]}]},{"t":"span","c":[" "]},{"t":"span","p":{"class":"syntax--meta syntax--brace syntax--square syntax--js"},"c":[{"t":"span","c":["["]}]}]}]},{"t":"div","p":{"class":"line"},"c":[{"t":"span","p":{"class":"syntax--source syntax--js"},"c":[{"t":"span","c":["        "]},{"t":"span","p":{"class":"syntax--meta syntax--function-call syntax--js"},"c":[{"t":"span","p":{"class":"syntax--support syntax--function syntax--js"},"c":[{"t":"span","c":["require"]}]},{"t":"span","p":{"class":"syntax--meta syntax--arguments syntax--js"},"c":[{"t":"span","p":{"class":"syntax--punctuation syntax--definition syntax--arguments syntax--begin syntax--bracket syntax--round syntax--js"},"c":[{"t":"span","c":["("]}]},{